{"parse":{"title":"Oil droplet","pageid":34353611,"revid":841412930,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BirdCone.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/BirdCone.png/220px-BirdCone.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"316\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/BirdCone.png/330px-BirdCone.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/BirdCone.png/440px-BirdCone.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"778\" data-file-height=\"1116\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:BirdCone.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Bird cone cell, including oil droplet.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Oil droplets</b> are found in the <a href=\"/wiki/Eye\" title=\"Eye\">eyes</a> of some animals, being located in the <a href=\"/wiki/Photoreceptor_cell\" title=\"Photoreceptor cell\">photoreceptor cells</a>. They are especially common in the eyes of <a href=\"/wiki/Diurnality\" title=\"Diurnality\">diurnal</a> (active during the day) <a href=\"/wiki/Reptile\" title=\"Reptile\">reptiles</a> (e.g. <a href=\"/wiki/Lizard\" title=\"Lizard\">lizards</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Turtle\" title=\"Turtle\">turtles</a>) and <a href=\"/wiki/Bird\" title=\"Bird\">birds</a> (see <a href=\"/wiki/Bird_vision\" title=\"Bird vision\">bird vision</a>), though are present in other taxa such as <a href=\"/wiki/Lungfish\" title=\"Lungfish\">lungfish</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> They are found in <a href=\"/wiki/Cone_cell\" title=\"Cone cell\">cone cells</a> far more often than in <a href=\"/wiki/Rod_cell\" title=\"Rod cell\">rods</a>, suggesting a role in <a href=\"/wiki/Colour_vision\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Colour vision\">colour vision</a>. Occurrence in rod cells may imply that they have been modified from a cone cell ancestor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Walls_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Walls-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> They occasionally occur in <a href=\"/wiki/Double_cone_(biology)\" title=\"Double cone (biology)\">double cones</a>/double rods.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Walls_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Walls-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Some oil droplets are <a href=\"/wiki/Colour\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Colour\">coloured</a>, while others appear colourless. They are located in the cone inner segment, where they intercept and filter <a href=\"/wiki/Light\" title=\"Light\">light</a> before it can pass through to the cone outer segment where the <a href=\"/wiki/Visual_pigment\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Visual pigment\">visual pigment</a> is.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Vorobyev_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Vorobyev-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Adaptation\" title=\"Adaptation\">adaptive advantage</a> of oil droplets is not firmly established. Coloured oil droplets have a cost in that they reduce the amount of light available to the <a href=\"/wiki/Visual_system\" title=\"Visual system\">visual system</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wilby_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Wilby-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> They also reduce the overlap in <a href=\"/wiki/Spectral_sensitivity\" title=\"Spectral sensitivity\">spectral sensitivity</a> between different types of cone (e.g. short <a href=\"/wiki/Wavelength\" title=\"Wavelength\">wavelength</a> sensitive, medium wavelength sensitive etc.). This can be a benefit because it increases the number of colours that can be discriminated, and calculations by Vorobyev (2003) support the hypothesis that this is of net benefit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Vorobyev_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Vorobyev-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Oil_droplet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Robinson, S.R. (1994). \"Early vertebrate color vision\". <i>Nature</i>. <b>367</b>: 121. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1038/367121a0\">10.1038/367121a0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Nature&amp;rft.atitle=Early+vertebrate+color+vision&amp;rft.volume=367&amp;rft.pages=121&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1038%2F367121a0&amp;rft.au=Robinson%2C+S.R.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOil+droplet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Walls-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Walls_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Walls_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Walls, G. (1942). <i>The Vertebrate Eye and its Adaptive Radiation</i>. MI, Bloomfield Hills: Cranbrook Institute of Science. pp.&#160;55\u201363.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Vertebrate+Eye+and+its+Adaptive+Radiation&amp;rft.place=MI%2C+Bloomfield+Hills&amp;rft.pages=55-63&amp;rft.pub=Cranbrook+Institute+of+Science&amp;rft.date=1942&amp;rft.aulast=Walls&amp;rft.aufirst=G.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOil+droplet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Vorobyev-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Vorobyev_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Vorobyev_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Vorobyev, M. (2003). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1691374\">\"Coloured oil droplets enhance colour discrimination\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Proc._R._Soc._Lond._B\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Proc. R. Soc. Lond. B\">Proc. R. Soc. Lond. B</a></i>. <b>270</b>: 1255\u20131261. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1098/rspb.2003.2381\">10.1098/rspb.2003.2381</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Central\" title=\"PubMed Central\">PMC</a>&#160;<span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1691374\">1691374</a>&#8239;<img alt=\"Freely accessible\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/9px-Lock-green.svg.png\" title=\"Freely accessible\" width=\"9\" height=\"14\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/14px-Lock-green.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/Lock-green.svg/18px-Lock-green.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"813\" /></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Proc.+R.+Soc.+Lond.+B&amp;rft.atitle=Coloured+oil+droplets+enhance+colour+discrimination&amp;rft.volume=270&amp;rft.pages=1255-1261&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1691374&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1098%2Frspb.2003.2381&amp;rft.au=Vorobyev%2C+M.&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1691374&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOil+droplet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Wilby-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Wilby_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Wilby D, Toomey MB, Olsson P, Frederiksen R, Cornwall MC, Oulton R, Kelber A, Corbo JC, Roberts NW (2015). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rsif.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/12/111/20150591\">\"Optics of cone photoreceptors in the chicken (<i>Gallus gallus domesticus</i>)\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=J._R._Soc._Interface&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"J. R. Soc. Interface (page does not exist)\">J. R. Soc. Interface</a></i>. <b>12</b>: 20150591. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1098/rsif.2015.0591\">10.1098/rsif.2015.0591</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=J.+R.+Soc.+Interface&amp;rft.atitle=Optics+of+cone+photoreceptors+in+the+chicken+%28Gallus+gallus+domesticus%29.&amp;rft.volume=12&amp;rft.pages=20150591&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1098%2Frsif.2015.0591&amp;rft.aulast=Wilby&amp;rft.aufirst=D&amp;rft.au=Toomey%2C+MB&amp;rft.au=Olsson%2C+P&amp;rft.au=Frederiksen%2C+R&amp;rft.au=Cornwall%2C+MC&amp;rft.au=Oulton%2C+R&amp;rft.au=Kelber%2C+A&amp;rft.au=Corbo%2C+JC&amp;rft.au=Roberts%2C+NW&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Frsif.royalsocietypublishing.org%2Fcontent%2F12%2F111%2F20150591&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOil+droplet\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1284\nCached time: 20180907220630\nCach